<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-12-14T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-12-14T16:36:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                    <head>306. Telegram From <gloss type="from">the Department of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">the Embassy in Pakistan</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d306fn1">Source: National Archives, RG 59, Central
                            Files 1970–73, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 27 INDIA–<gloss target="#t_PAK1">PAK</gloss>. Secret; Priority; <gloss target="#t_EXDIS1">Exdis</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>, cleared in the White
                            House by <persName corresp="#p_SHH1">Saunders</persName>, and approved
                            by <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>. Repeated to New Delhi
                            and Calcutta.</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1971-12-14T21:36:00+00:00">December 14, 1971,
                            2136Z</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>224704. If and when Bangla Desh and or Indian forces occupy Dacca, you should
                        not take any initiative to establish or encourage contact with them beyond
                        that which may be required in emergency situations to protect American lives
                        or to otherwise assure safety of your mission.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">
                                <hi rend="strong">Rogers</hi>
                            </persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>